translated: Eskång, Oskar Harald, medical practitioner, Nybro, born on December 1, 1900 in Aneby, Jönköping county, Sweden, firstborn of timber merchant Sven Johan E. and Frida Johans[i]on. Married in 1934 to registered nurse Inez Hillberg. They had three children: Catarina born in 1936, Annika in 1941, and Bodil in 1943. Oskar completed his high school education in Lund in 1919, and obtained his Bachelor of Medicine degree in 1924 and medical license in 1931, both from Lund University. He worked as assistant physician in Ekisjö in 1927, acting district physician in several districts from 1928-1932, resident physician at S:t Gertruds hospital in 1932, and established his own medical practice in Nybro in 1932. He was also acting deputy physician at sanatorium in Fur in 1933, at sanatorium in Eksjö in 1934, and a medical doctor at Lannaskede spa from 1935-1937, at Nybro spa in 1940. He was a physician in several departments for chronic diseases, school physician in multiple school districts, acting deputy physician at Växjö city hospital, and school physician at upper secondary school in 1938 and at county council's mental hospital in 1942. Oskar was also a member of the health committee in 1937 and the child welfare committee in 1942. He wrote a dedication for the pastor J. Waihlgren in Nybro on his 50th anniversary as a minister in 1962.
